Memberships
Looking for an exceptional golfing experience in Tampa? Join Countryway Golf Club as a member and enjoy unlimited access to our beautiful 18-hole golf course and practice facilities. We offer various membership options to fit your individual needs, whether you’re a seasoned golfer or just starting out.
Single – $850.00 Annually
Unlimited Greens Fees for One Player for one year from date of purchase
$10.00 Cart Fee per round
Junior – $425.00 Annually
Unlimited Greens Fees for One Player for one year from date of purchase
$10.00 Cart Fee per round
Husband & Wife – $1300.00 Annually
Unlimited Greens Fees for each player for one year from date of purchase
$10.00 Cart Fee per round
Family Membership – $1300.00 Annually
+ $200.00 per child
Unlimited Greens Fees for each player for one year from date of purchase
$10.00 Cart Fee per round
Passes are non-transferable. Prices do not include sales tax. Prices are subject to change without notice.

About Us
Countryway Golf Club is a challenging executive golf course with beautiful undulating greens and fairways with water hazards coming into play on 14 holes. Nationally known architect Steve Smyers designed Countryway’s par 61 course which has seven par 4’s and eleven par 3’s. Countryway is known for is affordable rates and was voted by the readers of the Daily Planet as the “Best Value Golf Course in Tampa Bay”.
Countryway is family owned by the Sherlock and Creighton families. Dave Creighton played professional hockey in the NHL for Boston, New York Rangers, Toronto and Chicago. His son Adam also played in the NHL for Buffalo, Chicago, New York Islanders, Tampa Bay and St. Louis.
